 </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <th>0</th>\n      <td>Baseline</td>\n      <td>4</td>\n      <td>0</td>\n      <td>1.758542</td>\n      <td>0.017800</td>\n      <td>1.0</td>\n      <td>-0.005132</td>\n      <td>0.015007</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>1</th>\n      <td>ML hard filter</td>\n      <td>1</td>\n      <td>5</td>\n      <td>2.273939</td>\n      <td>0.010623</td>\n      <td>1.0</td>\n      <td>-0.001124</td>\n      <td>0.040780</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>2</th>\n      <td>ML position scaling</td>\n      <td>4</td>\n      <td>0</td>\n      <td>1.902845</td>\n      <td>0.018891</td>\n      <td>1.0</td>\n      <td>-0.004776</td>\n      <td>0.015007</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Strategy Snapshot\n\n::: {#15ad227e .cell execution_count=6}\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=6}\n```{=html}\n<div>\n<style scoped>\n    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n        vertical-align: middle;\n    }\n\n    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n        vertical-align: top;\n    }\n\n    .dataframe thead th {\n        text-align: right;\n    }\n</style>\n<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n  <thead>\n    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n      <th></th>\n      <th>Field</th>\n      <th>Value</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <th>0</th>\n      <td>Strategy</td>\n      <td>Tuned baseline volatility and channel breakout</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>1</th>\n      <td>Data source</td>\n      <td>shinybroker / Interactive Brokers historical d...</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>2</th>\n      <td>Selected symbol</td>\n      <td>QQQ</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>3</th>\n      <td>Sample window</td>\n      <td>2021-04-26 to 2026-04-24</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>4</th>\n      <td>Status</td>\n      <td>Baseline strategy tuned and implemented</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Project Scope\n\n- Build a transparent breakout strategy with explicit entry and exit rules.\n- Backtest the strategy on historical price data using a repeatable Python workflow.\n- Log every trade so entries, exits, and holding periods are auditable.\n- Extend the baseline strategy with supervised learning tests for breakout quality, including a hard filter and the final position-scaling overlay.\n\nThe final baseline is a tuned `QQQ` channel-breakout strategy with explicit stop-loss, trailing-stop, timeout, and breakout-failure exits. On top of that baseline, the project adds a compact `QQQ`-only logistic model that uses breakout quality plus options-implied-volatility features. The report compares a hard model filter with a position-scaling overlay and uses the overlay as the final version because it keeps the breakout opportunity set while changing capital allocation.\n\n## What To Review\n\n- [Results](results.qmd) leads with the fixed October 2025-April 2026 holdout evaluation and performance graph.\n- [Asset Selection](asset-selection.qmd) explains the ETF universe and why `QQQ` became the showcase asset.\n- [Methodology](methodology.qmd) documents the final trading rules, labels, feature set, and parameter choices.\n- [Trade Log](trade-log.qmd) contains the blotter, ledger preview, and downloadable output files.\n- [Monitoring](monitoring.qmd) defines how to judge whether the strategy is still behaving as expected after deployment.\n- [About](about.qmd) introduces the project team.\n\n",
